FBIS4-2605 "drchi070_c_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-070 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 Central Eurasia Qian Qichen Meets Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Qian Qichen Meets Russian Deputy Foreign Minister OW1204073394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0655 GMT 12 Apr 94 OW1204073394 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- The series of visits scheduled to be exchanged between China and Russia this year will help further promote the relations between the two countries, said Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen . Qian made the statement during his meeting with visiting deputy Foreign Minister Alexsandr Panov of Russia here this morning. Qian and Panov exchanged views on bilateral relations and international issues of common concern. Qian said that Russia is a big country that plays an important role in world affairs, adding that China always puts its relations with Russia high on its foreign policy agenda. Qian said that there has been healthy and steady development recently in the bilateral relations, adding that the developing of good neighborly relations between the two countries not only conforms to the interests of the countries themselves, but also constitutes a stabilizing factor in the Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole. The Chinese vice-premier expressed his belief that the bilateral relations will be further developed though joint efforts. Panov expressed his satisfaction over the positive results of his current visit to China. He held that Russia-China relations will become better and better. Yesterday afternoon Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Dai Bingguo held talks with Panov on bilateral relations and other issues of common concern.
